<br>
 <p>Hareq Ghoulslayer, 54 Paladin<br>
Amnesty</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulandyalexandre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LandyAlexandre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 8:08:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> I am not privy to the officers discussions on this subject, so i dont know what has been brought up already and what has not.  I for one have had a hard time getting to know the regular crews from each of the guilds in the SGA in the time since we expanded the alliance to 4 guilds.  <br>
<br>
Currently i feel like i DO know quite a few people in each of the guilds, but i also feel like i have put a lot of effort into it.  Im wondering how much of our membership feels like they are ready to expand the alliance again.  It would be interesting to hear comments from the rest of you.  <br>
<br>
I will admit that i was a little uncomfortable with the expansion of the alliance to 4 guilds, but that now i am quite happy that it occurred.  <br>
<br>
It seems to me that we need to come up with a list of criteria that can be used to help guide us in our decision to expand or not.  Perhaps if we examine whether or not the current union is fulfilling its purpose and meeting its goals that will tell us whether we should be expanding.  These are just suggestions.  <br>
<br>
Im somewhat curious to know which (if any) particular guilds are already being considered for inclusion.  It almost seems like we need to agree on a procedure to be followed to include a new guild before we do in fact add any more.  <br>
<br>
Personally, I would say that i am ever so slightly in favor of a little more expansion at the present moment.  <br>
<br>
Landy Alexandre<br>
Spirit Guardians <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzenknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zenknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 8:23:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> Hey Guys<br>
<br>
Landy<br>
<br>
The guilds are <br>
<br>
Valiant Coalition<br>
Daywalkers<br>
Issuo Aggnatio (sp)<br>
<br>
As to your question about are we full filling the purpose of the SGA, I personally would have to give a resounding yes from the planar level side. We raid and group constantly.<br>
<br>
Anyway these are the guilds that I knoe of that are interested.<br>
<br>
Zen  <p>Zenknight Darkhorse,
53 Champion,
Warlord ,
Screaming Fist</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uholtthecleric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Holt the Cleric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 11:49:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> From the last Hate raid</span><hr size=1> If we had more guilds we would have been able to call them up when we needed reinforcements on Sunday.<br>
<br>
Also some other guilds that I know would be interested are<br>
<br>
Defender of the Faith<br>
Brightblade Knights<br>
<br>
<br>
As far as Daywalkers joining I have conflict with that personally, and will discuss that in private in game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utordaor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tordaor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 2:04:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> I realize I am fairly new, but I can't even remember the names of the guilds in the alliance.  I don't know most of my guild because they are all such a higher level than me.  The only people I really know are Jethinoria, Carradill, and Tildaien because they are RL friends.  I would like to meet the rest of the guilds but I haven't had a chance yet.  I suggest that we have a saryn guild alliance meeting sometime soon so every can get to know everyone else.  This could easily be held someplace like EFP becuase there are hardly any players in there at any given time.  A meeting on a weekend for those of us that have restricted game times (parents, work, etc.) would be great. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umyriahwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Myriahwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 3:33:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> Landy's idea about setting up certain criteria sounds good. Perhaps we can work out some simple test to see if we need to expand. The following is my first try to set this up.<br>
<br>
If the alliance is found lacking in anyone of the following areas, we should seriously consider adding a new member.<br>
<br>
1. Planes Raid personal; especially clerics, enchanters, monks, and rogues.<br>
<br>
2. Raid leadership.<br>
<br>
3. Events for all levels.<br>
<br>
4. Trade skill masters. <br>
<br>
5. Participants for SGA events.<br>
<br>
<br>
Well you get the idea.  Please feel free to add or subtract or overwise comment on this.<br>
<br>
Myriah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubamilbanebringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bamil Banebringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 6:21:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> Hareq, I would have liked to have seen some opinion on who you would like added, when these guilds could join our raids, and why.<br>
<br>
In fact, the reason we have not added another guild at this time is the lack of unity (or rather everyone seemingly abstaining) for one choice.<br>
<br>
So... what needs to happen for &quot;someone to make a decision&quot;??? In this thread name who you would like to see added, and why. Over 10 different guildnames have been brought up at one time or another. To differentiate these guilds we need our members to make some choices on who they would like to see join us.<br>
<br>
I had asked that this be discussed on your boards with your members and a decision be brought back here. I haven't seen any decisions from any of the 4 guilds, so let's move that discussion here.<br>
<br>
What will happen? We will invite the selected guilds to join us on a few of our raids to be sure they are what we expected them to be. At that time they will be invited.<br>
<br>
Bamil Banebringer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvainne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vainne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/1/01 3:11:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http--braggarts.shareplay.com-pics-Wythe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> I speak strongly FOR VC, Issu and Daywalkers, having grouped with several of their members during their formative years. In addition, I'd like to see Bethene's guild (whatever they are called) join the SGA.<br>
<br>
As with any guild, not every single person in them, (or in SF, SG, Amnesty, etc) is my favorite---I only mention this because Holt, please have a caution before dismissing one guild out of hand. Whatever your slight was, I recommend reconciling it between yourself and the party involved. <br>
<br>
The arguement against adding more members due to lack of coherency is a strong one, I agree. Except, this is the thing: at its core the SGA offers the possibility to do something small guilds cannot do on their own---that is, raid. This idea is bound to be popular.<br>
<br>
As long as any guild maintains the respect and loot rules set forth by the SGA, I would hope that their members would be included.<br>
<br>
If adding more bodies makes more work, then we need to set up procedures to streamline this. Database with member lists, Periodic meetings between guild officials, a prodedure for greivances, etc, etc. Not everyone in all of these guilds will use the SGA. For those that do (and may all they be enchanters and clerics :P) set up strict guidleines and there shouldnt be any problems. <p><b> ~The Nightblind Bard~
<b>~Amnesty, Saryrn~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulandyalexandre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LandyAlexandre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/1/01 6:56:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> I have grouped with numerous members and officers of the Valiant Coalition (VC) guild and was almost always pleasantly surprised with the quality of these players.  For this reason i was earnestly looking forward to the possibility of having them added to the SGA... <br>
<br>
However it would seem that the last few weeks have not been kind to VC.  Apparently, this guild may be about to disband after a failed attempt to ally/merge with Travellers of Norrath.  I have been told that their GL left the guild recently.  I know for a fact that Elian, the officer who initially signaled their interest in the SGA is no longer with them.  <br>
<br>
It is unfortunate that this happened to VC, but it does bring out the point that crafting an alliance can put a guild under stress.  If this past weekend's hate raid is any meaure of success, it seems clear that the SGA has been a real boon to our guilds' memberships.  Personally, I greatly enjoy the company of my SGA brethren, so feel i must urge that we proceed with care.  It would be a tremendous shame to have our attempts to expand the SGA lead to its reduction or demise.  <br>
<br>
Landy Alexandre<br>
Spirit Guardians <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhareq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hareq</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/1/01 7:07:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Hareq, I would have liked to have seen some opinion on who you would like added, when these guilds could join our raids, and why.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ok, you asked for it.<br>
<br>
1.  I was under the impression that there was a representative from each guild in the SGA council.  This representative was to vote on matters concerning inviting new guilds.  I don't see how hard this is ?  There are only 4 guilds now, that's four representatives.  Who's abstaining ?  Who hasn't voted ?<br>
<br>
2.  The only guilds that I have seen post on our message board for membership are VC and IA.  They're the only guilds that I know of that have also joined us on raids.  I think there needs to be set dates posted that other guilds can see as to when we will be inviting others.  The way it sits now, VC and IA and whoever else applies has no timeframe.  To be honest, they've been more than patient now, as it has appeared that we have been ignoring them.  I'd like to see 2 guilds or 1 guild every 2 months.  Have a section where new guilds apply.  Our representatives vote on them, if there are 7 guilds in the queue, then they vote on the 7 guilds, giving them a value of 1-7, where 7 is the guild they want in the most.  You total up everyone's points, and the two guilds with the most points gets invited.  Two months later, we do the same thing.  This time the guilds that were on the waiting list start with a preset 5 points, and we do the process over again.  If for some reason 50% of the representatives deem that a guild should not be invited, then they should be informed of such immediately, and removed from the voting.  <br>
<br>
3.  I hear people saying that &quot;we're big enough&quot;.  When do we stop inviting people ?  My response to that is, why ?  The SGA is an alliance, it's not one big guild.  So what if we have 10 guilds in it ?  The WHOLE PREMISE behind the SGA was to allow smaller guilds accomplish things that they COULD NOT accomplish on their own.  It wasn't designed to be just big enough to do stuff on it's own.<br>
<br>
If the SGA is to become only so big then stop allowing other guilds to join, then the SGA has become exactly what I have attempted to avoid.  It will be no better than a larger guild that descriminates against classes and levels and size.  We'll be doing raids and not inviting friends.<br>
<br>
4.  People say we're inviting guilds too fast.  That they haven't gotten to know everyone else yet.  Do you know everyone in your own guild ?  I don't.  Does this stop me from treating them as friends when I see them ?  No.  Does this mean Amnesty is too big ?  No.  Have I met and made friends with a lot of new people because of SGA ?  Yes.  <br>
<br>
5.  Diadem will be getting his Epic here shortly.  I plan on setting up a raid to take out the General for this weekend.  That will push the total of Epics to two.  That's two more than I ever thought we would have by now.  Is there anyone else that thought the SGA would be so close to taking out VS or Trak at this point ?<br>
<br>
6.  Word has it that Hareq doesn't attend any raids that he doesn't lead.  Is this true ?  I think not.  Did I not go to Kael and help Malleolus ?  How about when I helped Holt on his KK raid ?  Zenknight's raid in Kithicor Forrest ?<br>
<br>
I think you're misinterpretting my intent.  The problem is if I attend a raid, then people expect me to lead it.  I don't want to lead every raid.  I want others to lead them as well.<br>
<br>
I forsee a time when Zenknight is leading a raid into Hate, and I'm helping lead several groups into Velks. Lab.  Across the world Boofa is leading a group to take out the Black Reavers.<br>
<br>
So far Krytog, Zenknight and Lingling have stepped up big time, and have led some very successful raids.  I applaud them on their hard work.  It is very difficult to lead a raid, and if you haven't tried, I suggest you do. <p>Hareq Ghoulslayer, 54 Paladin<br>
Amnesty</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzenknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zenknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/1/01 7:30:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> I think we get baratis's guild in now. VC is in turmoil at the moment and may need a cooling off period.<br>
<br>
Hareq <br>
<br>
I don't thnk we have an issue with you comming on a raid and people thinking your going to lead. If that's keeping you from going to any of my raids then don't worry about it. Unless I know that you have more knowledge of a zone then I do your just a member of the team. Kith for me was different, I knew that your knowledge of that target was better then mine. So don't keep yourself from going because of that.<br>
<br>
The last fear raid worked like this. Holt had the idea. I initially lead the raid and got people there. I passed off the leadership mantel to Ling, Elektra and Henklin. They know the zone much better then I do, they know what needs to be done to break and pull. We shared the responsibilities and had a great raid.<br>
<br>
SO don't assume your going to mess something up by showing, being one of the highest level SGA tanks makes you valuable on all the raids.<br>
<br>
Zen   <p>Zenknight Darkhorse,
